1. CLAUDE (claude.ai)
─────────────────────
Role: Design, development, and documentation partner.

Claude was used to design and build the entire TrueNoise backend and website
from scratch — the FastAPI backend, the Supabase database schema, all four
website pages (index, about, methodology, data), the contact form integration,
and this documentation. Claude also produced the DEPLOY.md handoff document
for Xcode Claude and the WAV_PROCESSING_BRIEF.md for future development.

Claude is not a running service — it does not host anything or run any code.
It is a tool used during development. You return to Claude when you need to
build new features, fix bugs, update pages, or generate new documentation.

Current model: Claude Sonnet 4.6 (claude.ai)
Xcode integration: Claude Code (separate instance, used inside Xcode for
iOS app development)


2. GITHUB (github.com)
