3. RENDER (render.com)
──────────────────────
Role: Backend API server — the engine that receives data from the iOS app
and serves aggregated data to the dashboard.

Render runs the Python FastAPI application (main.py) as a live web service.
When the iOS app uploads a CSV session file, it POSTs to Render. When the
dashboard loads, it calls Render's API endpoints to fetch the data displayed
on screen. When a visitor clicks "Download CSV" on the data page, their
browser fetches the data from Render.

Render is on the free tier, which means it spins down after 15 minutes of
inactivity. UptimeRobot pings it every 5 minutes to prevent this.

Render connects to GitHub — when you push a change to main.py or
requirements.txt on GitHub, you trigger a new deployment on Render from
the Render dashboard (Manual Deploy → Deploy latest commit).

Service name: aircraft-noise-tracker-api (legacy name, functions correctly)
Live API URL: https://aircraft-noise-tracker-api.onrender.com
Key endpoints:
  GET  /health                              — confirms the service is running
  POST /api/v1/upload-session               — receives CSV from iOS app
  GET  /api/v1/dashboard-summary            — powers the dashboard
  GET  /api/v1/sessions                     — lists all sessions
  GET  /api/v1/sessions/{id}/observations   — observations for one session
Plan: Free tier
Database connection: Supabase (via DATABASE_URL environment variable)


4. SUPABASE (supabase.com)
──────────────────────────
Project: truenoise
Role: Permanent PostgreSQL database — stores all observation data.

Supabase is where all the noise measurement data lives permanently.
Unlike Render's free tier (which has ephemeral local storage), Supabase
data persists indefinitely — through Render restarts, redeployments, and
sleep cycles.

The database has two tables:
  observations — one row per measurement (entry or track event). Every
    column from the app CSV is stored here, including psychoacoustic
    metrics, aircraft identifiers, GPS coordinates, and health impact labels.
  sessions — one row per uploaded session with pre-computed summary
    statistics (N65, N70, N80, recovery deficit, event density, peak values).

Render connects to Supabase using the DATABASE_URL environment variable
(set in Render's Environment settings). This is the Supabase Transaction
Pooler URL on port 6543 — required because Render's async server needs
connection pooling.

The database has a unique index on (session_id, timestamp, callsign) in
the observations table, which prevents duplicate rows if the same CSV is
uploaded more than once.

Account: Google account (marty's Gmail)
Dashboard: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/wpxmrlbkifawlfrmbnmf
Plan: Free tier (no expiry)
Connection string: stored in Render environment variables (do not share)


