──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CNAME
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A single-line file containing "truenoise.org". GitHub Pages reads this file
to know which custom domain to serve the site on. Without it, the site would
only be accessible at the github.io URL. Do not edit or delete this file.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DEPLOY.md
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The technical handoff document for Xcode Claude. Contains the current live
API URL, the exact CSV column format the backend expects, a complete Swift
URLSession code example for POSTing a CSV from the iOS app, a retry strategy
using UserDefaults for failed uploads, all API endpoint descriptions, and the
database schema summary. This is the primary reference document for anyone
building the iOS upload feature. Updated May 2026.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
WAV_PROCESSING_BRIEF.md
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Technical specification for a planned future feature: offline WAV file
analysis. Describes how to process pre-recorded audio files through the
existing psychoacoustic pipeline to generate session CSVs identical in
format to live monitoring sessions. Written for Xcode Claude. Covers the
AVAudioFile reading approach, chunk processing, timestamp handling, ADS-B
correlation limitations, calibration considerations, and a list of new
UI components required. No backend changes are needed for this feature.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
about.html
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The About page at truenoise.org/about.html. Tells the story of how and why
TrueNoise was founded (Marty Krizan, Ashbrook, Severn, MD), describes the
five founding principles (rigorous methodology, published evidence, open data,
independence, collaboration over confrontation), and hosts the contact form
that forwards submissions to Marty's email via Formspree. Includes full
responsive navigation consistent with the rest of the site.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data.html
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The data download page at truenoise.org/data.html. Shows live observation
counts pulled from the Render API, displays an early-stage dataset notice,
and provides a Download CSV button that fetches all observations from the
database and generates a properly formatted CSV file in the visitor's browser.
Includes a full column definitions table and an attribution block with a
ready-to-cite reference format. Operator names and aircraft identifiers are
included in the download (full dataset for researchers), even though they
are omitted from the public dashboard view.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
index.html
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The homepage and health impact dashboard at truenoise.org. Pulls live data
from the Render API on page load and displays: N70 event count, recovery
deficit count, peak loudness in sone, peak dBA, three health research
citation blocks (HYENA, RANCH, WHO), a recovery deficit dot visualization,
noise event summary cards, an aircraft breakdown table grouped by type and
flight phase (no operator names shown), and an hourly event distribution
bar chart. Falls back to sample data if the API is unreachable. Fully
responsive with hamburger navigation on mobile.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
main.py
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The FastAPI Python backend application that runs on Render. Handles all
server-side logic: receiving CSV uploads from the iOS app, parsing the
tab- or comma-separated data, inserting observations into Supabase with
duplicate prevention, computing session summary statistics (N65/N70/N80,
recovery deficit, event density), and serving the dashboard API endpoints.
Uses psycopg (version 3) for PostgreSQL connectivity. This is the file
you edit when changing API behavior, adding new endpoints, or modifying
how data is stored or aggregated. After editing, commit to GitHub and
trigger a Manual Deploy on Render.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
methodology.html
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
The methodology page at truenoise.org/methodology.html. A technically
rigorous nine-section document covering: hardware specifications (PoP Voice
lavalier microphone, iPhone A-series silicon), iOS audio capture in
.measurement mode, the IEC 61672 A-weighting filter implementation with
exact pole frequencies, FFT and 1/3-octave band analysis using Apple's
vDSP framework, psychoacoustic metrics (Zwicker loudness, sharpness,
annoyance), per-device calibration approach, validation results against
the TA657A Type 2 reference meter (1.4 dB agreement on live A320 overflight),
and an honest six-point limitations section. Written to withstand technical
scrutiny. Includes a right-side section navigation on desktop.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
render.yaml
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Render deployment configuration file. Specifies the service type (web),
runtime (Python), build command (pip install -r requirements.txt), and
start command (uvicorn main:app). Render reads this file when deploying.
The disk configuration in this file is no longer used (Supabase replaced
the local SQLite approach), but the file remains for reference. Environment
variables (DATABASE_URL) are set directly in the Render dashboard, not here.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
requirements.txt
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Python package dependencies for the backend. Lists the four libraries Render
installs when deploying: fastapi (the web framework), uvicorn (the ASGI
server that runs FastAPI), python-multipart (required for CSV file uploads),
and psycopg[binary] (PostgreSQL database driver for Supabase connectivity).
When adding new Python functionality to main.py that requires a new library,
add it here and redeploy.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
runtime.txt
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Specifies the Python version for Render to use. Contains "python-3.11.9".
This file was created to prevent Render from defaulting to Python 3.14,
which was incompatible with several dependencies during initial deployment.
If Render continues to ignore this file (as it did during setup), the
Python version can also be set in Render's dashboard settings.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
upload-test.html
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
A simple developer utility page used to manually test CSV uploads to the
Render API without needing the iOS app. Presents a file picker and an
"Upload to API" button. Used during development to confirm the upload
endpoint was working correctly and to seed the database with real session
data. Not linked from the public website but remains accessible at
truenoise.org/upload-test.html. Can be used anytime you want to manually
upload a session CSV.


