PART 3: DATA FLOW SUMMARY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

HOW DATA GETS IN:
  iOS app (Aircraft Noise Tracker)
    → POST CSV to Render API (/api/v1/upload-session)
    → Render parses CSV, computes summaries, stores in Supabase
    → Supabase persists data permanently

HOW DATA GETS OUT (dashboard):
  Visitor loads truenoise.org (served by GitHub Pages)
    → Browser calls Render API (/api/v1/dashboard-summary)
    → Render queries Supabase, returns aggregated JSON
    → Browser renders data into the dashboard

HOW DATA GETS OUT (download):
  Visitor clicks Download CSV on data.html
    → Browser calls Render API (/api/v1/sessions then /observations)
    → Render queries Supabase, returns all rows
    → Browser assembles CSV and triggers file download

HOW CONTACT FORMS WORK:
  Visitor submits About page form
    → Browser POSTs directly to Formspree
    → Formspree emails Marty
    → No Render or Supabase involvement


