PART 4: THINGS TO REMEMBER
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CREDENTIALS AND ACCOUNTS:
  All service accounts use either Marty's Google account or GitHub account
  for login. The Supabase database password and connection string are stored
  only in Render's Environment settings — do not store them anywhere else.

DOMAIN RENEWAL:
  truenoise.org and stopsevernnoise.org renew annually through GoDaddy.
  Set a calendar reminder — if a domain lapses, the site goes down.

SUPABASE FREE TIER:
  Supabase's free tier has no expiry date for the database itself, but the
  project may be paused after 90 days of inactivity (no API calls). As long
  as UptimeRobot is running and the dashboard is receiving occasional visits,
  this will not be an issue.

RENDER FREE TIER:
  Render's free tier is sufficient for current traffic. If the dashboard
  gains significant public attention and response times become an issue,
  consider upgrading to Render Starter ($7/month) for always-on service.

WHEN YOU MAKE CHANGES:
  Frontend (HTML files): edit on GitHub → auto-deploys to truenoise.org
  Backend (main.py, requirements.txt): edit on GitHub → Manual Deploy on Render
  Database schema: edit via Supabase SQL Editor → no redeployment needed

